{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864709935,"sessionID":"ses_2863851b4ffeM3xx74NGBPXISD","part":{"id":"prt_d79c84c360017Upk8w5BsplfZl","messageID":"msg_d79c83bd5001PIr38jkIGSLRow","sessionID":"ses_2863851b4ffeM3xx74NGBPXISD","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_6219376e5ed848018480d100","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## Summary\n\nEnhance and properly encapsulate the DockerService class in the AgentCube CLI to provide robust Docker image building, pushing, and management capabilities.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe `DockerService` class provides Docker operations for the AgentCube CLI, used during the `pack` and `build` commands. Currently implemented with basic functionality, it needs enhancement to fully match the design specifications and provide production-ready Docker integration.\n\n### Goal\n\nEnhance DockerService to:\n1. Provide comprehensive Docker image management (build, push, pull, remove, tag)\n2. Add proper error handling and validation\n3. Support build arguments and proxy settings\n4. Enable image inspection and metadata retrieval\n5. Support registry authentication and image tagging\n6. Add progress tracking and verbose logging\n\n### Value\n\n- **Reliable Builds**: Robust error handling for Docker operations\n- **Registry Support**: Push to private/public registries with authentication\n- **Image Management**: Full lifecycle management (build, tag, push, inspect, remove)\n- **Flexible Configuration**: Build args, proxy support, custom tags\n- **Debugging**: Detailed logging for troubleshooting builds\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| DockerService class | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Enhanced Docker operations |\n| CLI integration | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Docker-related CLI options |\n| Unit tests | `tests/test_docker_service.py` | Test coverage |\n| Documentation | docstrings | API documentation |\n\n### Current API (to be enhanced)\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n    def push_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n    def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n    @staticmethod\n    def generate_python_dockerfile(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n    @staticmethod\n    def generate_java_dockerfile(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n    @staticmethod\n    def write_dockerfile(workspace_path: Path, content: str) -> Path: ...\n```\n\n### Enhanced API (proposed additions)\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    # Existing methods (keep as-is)\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n    def build_image(...) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def get_image_info(...) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def push_image(...) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def remove_image(...) -> bool: ...\n    @staticmethod\n    def generate_python_dockerfile(...) -> str: ...\n    @staticmethod\n    def generate_java_dockerfile(...) -> str: ...\n    @staticmethod\n    def write_dockerfile(...) -> Path: ...\n\n    # New methods to add\n    def pull_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    \n    def tag_image(\n        self,\n        source_image: str,\n        target_image: str,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    \n    def list_images(\n        self,\n        filters: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n    \n    def image_exists(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n    \n    def get_image_history(self, image_name: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n    \n    def prune_images(\n        self,\n        filters: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \n    def get_docker_info(self) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \n    def get_docker_version(self) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Docker Compose integration\n- Multi-stage build optimization\n- BuildKit advanced features\n- Container runtime (running containers)\n- Volume management\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `docker>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python | Existing |\n| `docker[sdk]` | Docker SDK | Existing |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich output | Existing |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **cli-toolkit/design.md** — DockerService class design\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Docker integration requirements\n- **AR-020 (pack)** — Uses DockerService for Dockerfile generation\n- **AR-021 (build)** — Uses DockerService for image building\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **PackRuntime** — Dockerfile generation\n2. **BuildRuntime** — Image building and pushing\n3. **PublishRuntime** — Image preparation for deployment\n4. **End users** — Direct Docker operations via CLI\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Docker not installed | High | Check availability before operations |\n| Docker daemon not running | High | Clear error message, troubleshooting guide |\n| Build failures | Medium | Detailed error parsing, suggested fixes |\n| Registry auth failures | Medium | Clear credential error messages |\n| Large image sizes | Low | Size information in build results |\n| Network issues | Medium | Timeout handling, retry support |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Enhanced DockerService (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Extend the existing DockerService class with additional methods and improved error handling.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Minimal code changes\n- Backward compatible\n- Leverages existing patterns\n- Direct Docker SDK access\n\n**Cons**:\n- Class may grow large\n- Some methods may not be used\n\n**Decision**: Selected — aligns with incremental enhancement approach.\n\n### Option 2: Separate Docker Modules\n\n**Approach**: Split into DockerBuildService, DockerPushService, DockerImageService.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Single Responsibility Principle\n- Easier testing\n- Smaller units\n\n**Cons**:\n- More refactoring\n- Breaking changes\n- Over-engineering for current needs\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — current scale doesn't warrant splitting.\n\n### Option 3: Use docker-py Instead of docker SDK\n\n**Approach**: Replace docker SDK with lighter docker-py library.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Smaller dependency\n- Simpler API\n\n**Cons**:\n- Missing high-level features\n- Rewriting working code\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — current SDK provides needed functionality.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core Enhancement\n- [ ] Enhance `build_image` with better error handling\n- [ ] Add image size formatting to build result\n- [ ] Add build time tracking\n- [ ] Add stream output for verbose mode\n\n### Phase 2: Registry Support\n- [ ] Implement `pull_image` method\n- [ ] Implement `tag_image` method\n- [ ] Enhance `push_image` with retag support\n- [ ] Add registry URL parsing\n\n### Phase 3: Image Management\n- [ ] Implement `list_images` method\n- [ ] Implement `image_exists` method\n- [ ] Implement `get_image_history` method\n- [ ] Implement `prune_images` method\n\n### Phase 4: Docker Info\n- [ ] Implement `get_docker_info` method\n- [ ] Implement `get_docker_version` method\n\n### Phase 5: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for all existing methods\n- [ ] Unit tests for new methods\n- [ ] Mock-based tests for Docker SDK\n- [ ] Integration tests (optional, requires Docker)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Docker Availability Check\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| DA-001 | Docker running | Returns True, logs debug message |\n| DA-002 | Docker not running | Returns False, logs warning |\n| DA-003 | Docker not installed | Returns False, logs error |\n\n### Image Build\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| IB-001 | Valid Dockerfile | Returns image_id, tags, build_time |\n| IB-002 | Invalid Dockerfile | Raises ValueError with details |\n| IB-003 | Build with proxy | Sets HTTP_PROXY, HTTPS_PROXY build args |\n| IB-004 | Build with custom tag | Tags image correctly |\n| IB-005 | Build verbose mode | Streams build output |\n\n### Image Push\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| IP-001 | Push to registry | Returns pushed_image, push_time |\n| IP-002 | Push with auth | Logs in before push |\n| IP-003 | Push without auth | Pushes without login |\n| IP-004 | Push non-existent image | Raises ValueError |\n\n### Image Management\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| IM-001 | List images | Returns list of image dicts |\n| IM-002 | Image exists (yes) | Returns True |\n| IM-003 | Image exists (no) | Returns False |\n| IM-004 | Remove image | Returns True on success |\n| IM-005 | Pull image | Returns pulled image info |\n\n### Dockerfile Generation\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| DG-001 | Python agent | Valid Dockerfile with pip install |\n| DG-002 | Java agent | Valid multi-stage Dockerfile |\n| DG-003 | With requirements | Copies requirements.txt |\n| DG-004 | Custom entrypoint | Uses custom CMD |\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### Build Image Flow\n\n```\nbuild_image()\n    │\n    ├─→ Validate inputs\n    │   ├─→ Check dockerfile_path exists\n    │   └─→ Check context_path exists\n    │\n    ├─→ Create Docker client\n    │   └─→ docker.from_env()\n    │\n    ├─→ Build image\n    │   ├─→ client.images.build()\n    │   ├─→ Pass build_args (proxy, etc.)\n    │   └─→ Stream output if verbose\n    │\n    ├─→ Collect results\n    │   ├─→ image_id\n    │   ├─→ tags\n    │   ├─→ size (via _format_size)\n    │   └─→ build_time\n    │\n    └─→ Return result dict\n```\n\n### Push Image Flow\n\n```\npush_image()\n    │\n    ├─→ Get Docker client\n    │\n    ├─→ Authenticate if credentials provided\n    │   └─→ client.login()\n    │\n    ├─→ Get image\n    │   └─→ client.images.get()\n    │\n    ├─→ Retag if registry_url provided\n    │   └─→ image.tag()\n    │\n    ├─→ Push image\n    │   └─→ image.push(stream=True)\n    │\n    ├─→ Stream logs (verbose)\n    │\n    └─→ Return {status, image, push_time}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n```python\ndef build_image(self, ...):\n    try:\n        client = docker.from_env()\n        # ... build logic\n    except docker.errors.BuildError as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Build failed: {e}\")\n        raise ValueError(f\"Docker build failed: {e}\")\n    except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Docker API error: {e}\")\n        raise ValueError(f\"Docker API error: {e}\")\n    except FileNotFoundError as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"File not found: {e}\")\n        raise ValueError(f\"Dockerfile not found: {e}\")\n```\n\n### Logging Strategy\n\n```python\ndef __init__(self, verbose: bool = False):\n    self.verbose = verbose\n    self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n    \n    if verbose:\n        logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n    else:\n        logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| Core Enhancement | 2-3 hours |\n| Registry Support | 2 hours |\n| Image Management | 2-3 hours |\n| Docker Info | 1 hour |\n| Testing | 3-4 hours |\n| **Total** | **10-13 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Existing Implementation Status\n\nThe DockerService has a working implementation:\n\n1. **DockerService** (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`): 262 lines\n2. **Static methods**: `generate_python_dockerfile`, `generate_java_dockerfile`, `write_dockerfile`\n3. **Instance methods**: `check_docker_available`, `build_image`, `get_image_info`, `push_image`, `remove_image`\n\n### Current Gaps\n\n1. **Missing methods**: `pull_image`, `tag_image`, `list_images`, `image_exists`, `get_image_history`, `prune_images`, `get_docker_info`, `get_docker_version`\n2. **Build result**: Missing `size` and `build_time` fields\n3. **Push result**: Missing `push_time` field\n4. **Verbose streaming**: Build/push output not streamed to logs\n5. **Image tagging**: `tag_image` method in design spec not implemented\n6. **Registry retag**: Missing logic to retag image for registry\n\n### Implementation Priority\n\n1. **High**: Enhance build_image result (size, build_time)\n2. **High**: Add push_time to push_image result\n3. **Medium**: Add pull_image method\n4. **Medium**: Add tag_image method\n5. **Medium**: Add list_images, image_exists methods\n6. **Low**: Add Docker info methods\n7. **Low**: Add prune_images method","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/docker_service.py\">\nERROR [131:23] \"errors\" is not a known a